# 2. ふたつの才能

Honami: That was a good meeting. We got to hear quite a lot of news today.
Saki: Yeah! I was wondering which we'd get to hear about, our debut or that festival. I can't believe we got to hear about both!
Ichika: Me neither. Especially when we heard what we'll be doing for our debut single...
Ichika: He really wants you and me to write it together, Saki...
Honami: You want Saki and Ichika to write it together...?
Ichika: Together...? Why is that?
Ichika: Saki always handles the music... So, wouldn't it be better to leave that in her hands...?
Shindo: Yes, I considered that option.
Shindo: The public gets its first impression of a band through its debut single. Which is why I thought about having you go with the process you've employed until now.
Shindo: But I decided against that. Instead of business as usual, I want you all to show everyone what Leo/need is like after you've reached the next level.
Honami: After we've reached the next level...?
Shiho: Can you elaborate a little further...?
Shindo: As things currently stand, Leo/need's debut takes first priority over everything else at this company for this part of the fiscal year.
Saki: First priority...?
Shindo: We plan to inject all our resources into coming up with the best marketing campaign for your band.
Honami: What...?!
Shindo: Which is why Mr. Shimizu from Starry Music, our parent company, was here. To discuss that very matter.
Shindo: In return for receiving a share of the distribution rights to Leo/need's debut single, they've agreed to help us with your marketing campaign.
Shiho: I see...
Shindo: Yes, and Mr. Shimizu also holds you in high regard.
Shindo: Starry Music will be giving you its spot on the digital billboards, as well as funding our ad campaigns centered around social media.
Saki: Billboards...! That means... This is like a super duper huge deal...!
Shindo: Yes, it is.
Shindo: To be honest, I wasn't expecting them to come up with so much money for us.
Shindo: But if things go well, your song is going to reach a lot of ears.
Shindo: In other words, you'll become household names overnight.
Ichika & Saki: ...
Shindo: Normally, we'd give a band more time to flesh out their music. And you ladies are still just getting on your feet.
Shindo: My original plan was to begin with having you become more experienced by playing shows and releasing more songs. Then, I would've started a big marketing campaign.
Shindo: But between the decisions that were made during our meeting the other day and Starry Music agreeing to join us in this endeavor...
Shindo: I came to believe that now is Leo/need's chance to take on a big challenge such as this.
Honami & Shiho: ...!
Shindo: The music you've produced up until now has been excellent.
Shindo: But I believe you can still go higher. I want to see Leo/need produce a song that can move the hearts of even more people.
Shindo: I believe Ms. Tenma and Ms. Hoshino will be able to achieve that by putting their individual talents together.
Saki: Me and Ichi...?
Shindo: Yes.
Shindo: Your songs have this warmth to them, Ms. Tenma. It's like you're able to show the listener real empathy.
Shindo: Your songs, Ms. Hoshino, are a little rough around the edges, but they have this charm to them because of how you always try to make your feelings crystal clear.
Shindo: Which is where this idea comes from. If Leo/need is able to join these two pieces in producing music, then I feel that your band is going to sound like it's taken another step forward.
Shindo: By doing so, I believe you'll be able to reach more people. In other words, Leo/need's music will be on a whole new level.
Shindo: Which will surely make your debut single an enormous success.
Saki: Our music...? The next level...?
Shindo: Yes.
Shindo: I'll look forward to hearing what you come up with.
Ichika: The next level...
Ichika: Can we really accomplish that...?
Saki: We'll be fine, Ichi! This is us we're talking about!
Honami: I agree. I also believe you two will do just fine.
Shiho: So do I, but...
Shiho: Compared to Ichika, aren't you being a little too optimistic about this, Saki?
Saki: Hehe. No way! Ichi and I've got this!
Shiho: Does that mean you already know what you wanna do?
Saki: Hmm... Not exactly...
Saki: But I feel like Ichi and I are unstoppable when we're together!
Ichika: Saki...
Saki: And it's not like Mr. Shindo would tell us to do this if he didn't think we could handle it, right?
Ichika: Yeah, true...
Ichika: And I agree. You and I should do just fine, Saki.
Saki: Yeah...!
Saki: Just wait, Shiho, Hona! We're gonna write the best debut single ever!
Shiho: Alright, we're counting on you.
Honami: Hehe. Good luck.
